WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

2
00:00:14.430 --> 00:00:16.870
Mariabell's dead...

3
00:00:17.430 --> 00:00:22.477
The West and the East must unite
in the struggle for humanity's survival.

4
00:00:22.560 --> 00:00:24.630
Against the Demon Lords.

5
00:00:25.900 --> 00:00:31.390
Even though there is no other way
to protect humanity...

6
00:00:32.020 --> 00:00:34.860
Hope is lost.

7
00:00:36.650 --> 00:00:38.070
Please don't feel resentful.

8
00:00:40.070 --> 00:00:41.490
Have faith...

9
00:00:43.150 --> 00:00:44.217
Yeah...

10
00:00:44.300 --> 00:00:46.167
I understand.

11
00:00:46.250 --> 00:00:50.040
I'm not sure how much
time remains for me.

12
00:00:50.750 --> 00:00:54.630
I can only pin my hopes
on that sliver of hope now...

13
00:01:00.980 --> 00:01:05.110
Humanity. hero. demon lord...

14
00:01:06.640 --> 00:01:11.510
I'm done playing nice. Luminus.

15
00:01:23.710 --> 00:01:26.407
More than a month has passed
since the ruin expedition.

16
00:01:26.490 --> 00:01:29.790
and the Mariabell incident has been
classified as an "accident"...

17
00:01:30.290 --> 00:01:31.997
I imagine the Kingdom of Seltrosso

18
00:01:32.080 --> 00:01:34.147
doesn't want to
make public the fact

19
00:01:34.230 --> 00:01:36.920
that its princess attacked
an ally. either.

20
00:01:38.830 --> 00:01:42.470
Granville Rosso remains eerily silent...

21
00:01:43.970 --> 00:01:46.177
Although Yuuki hasn't made
any notable moves either.

22
00:01:46.260 --> 00:01:49.350
there's no doubt he's still
working behind the scenes...

23
00:01:50.850 --> 00:01:53.600
That said. it's not all bad.

24
00:01:54.310 --> 00:01:56.857
Now that Mariabell
is no longer controlling the Council.

25
00:01:56.940 --> 00:02:01.490
they've turned to us... or rather. to me.
for a new figure to rally around.

26
00:02:02.550 --> 00:02:03.637
Phew...

27
00:02:03.720 --> 00:02:06.720
So. Tempest is now the largest
faction in the Council...

28
00:02:07.490 --> 00:02:11.787
Notice. there are many challenges ahead
for us on the international front.

29
00:02:11.870 --> 00:02:15.167
Oh. well. Becoming the largest
faction in the Council

30
00:02:15.250 --> 00:02:17.677
is a big step toward our ideals.

31
00:02:17.760 --> 00:02:18.500
Right?

32
00:02:19.900 --> 00:02:22.010
Shall we move on to business. then?

33
00:03:49.300 --> 00:03:52.010
THAT TIME I GOT REINCARNATED
AS A SLIME SEASON 4

34
00:03:52.370 --> 00:03:53.607
EPISODE 84: THE EVOLVING TEMPEST

35
00:03:53.690 --> 00:03:56.220
EPISODE 84: THE EVOLVING TEMPEST
Everyone. thank you for gathering here today!

36
00:03:56.730 --> 00:03:59.150
I have big news to share with you all.

37
00:03:59.980 --> 00:04:02.317
Henceforth. our Tempest will be...

38
00:04:02.400 --> 00:04:04.950
...stepping into a new stage!

39
00:04:05.780 --> 00:04:07.657
Stepping into a new stage?

40
00:04:07.740 --> 00:04:09.527
Are we going to have another festival?

41
00:04:09.610 --> 00:04:11.580
No. we're not!

42
00:04:12.960 --> 00:04:17.167
Tempest is currently the largest
faction in the Council.

43
00:04:17.250 --> 00:04:22.917
which means forming deep ties with
human societies in the Western world.

44
00:04:23.000 --> 00:04:26.797
Therefore. it is time for
our country to evolve.

45
00:04:26.880 --> 00:04:29.427
We will make Tempest
a constitutional state!

46
00:04:29.510 --> 00:04:31.427
A constitutional state?

47
00:04:31.510 --> 00:04:36.687
What does that mean. Master Rimuru?

48
00:04:36.770 --> 00:04:39.510
It means a nation organized
according to the law.

49
00:04:39.990 --> 00:04:43.437
Consider the law to be
the rules of the state.

50
00:04:43.520 --> 00:04:46.987
and bear in mind that those rules
take precedence in everything.

51
00:04:47.070 --> 00:04:49.237
Even over me. of course.

52
00:04:49.320 --> 00:04:50.827
Even over you. Master Rimuru?!

53
00:04:50.910 --> 00:04:52.827
Please hold on a minute...

54
00:04:52.910 --> 00:04:56.660
What would happen if you were to violate
that so-called law. Master Rimuru?

55
00:04:57.160 --> 00:04:59.077
Of course. I will be judged.

56
00:04:59.160 --> 00:05:00.787
I cannot accept that!

57
00:05:00.870 --> 00:05:04.047
Do we really have to go
to that extent to change?!

58
00:05:04.130 --> 00:05:06.510
Well. please calm down now.

59
00:05:08.300 --> 00:05:12.927
Monsters are strong compared
to humans and pose a threat.

60
00:05:13.010 --> 00:05:16.807
If such monsters adopt
the rules of human society.

61
00:05:16.890 --> 00:05:19.890
we can show them that we're safe.

62
00:05:20.320 --> 00:05:21.977
This is a crucial step toward...

63
00:05:22.060 --> 00:05:25.310
...the world Monster-and-Man
Cooperative Alliance that I aim for.

64
00:05:26.820 --> 00:05:29.650
Well. let's break down
the details right away!

65
00:05:30.080 --> 00:05:32.527
As I said earlier. to become
a nation governed by the law.

66
00:05:32.610 --> 00:05:35.577
we will adopt a system that
divides power into three branches.

67
00:05:35.660 --> 00:05:39.080
This is a principle called
the Separation of Powers.

68
00:05:39.520 --> 00:05:40.877
Here it is!

69
00:05:40.960 --> 00:05:42.377
Separation...

70
00:05:42.460 --> 00:05:43.960
...of powers?

71
00:05:44.500 --> 00:05:47.877
It consists of three branches:
the Legislative. which makes laws.

72
00:05:47.960 --> 00:05:50.677
the Executive. which governs
the nation according to those laws.

73
00:05:50.760 --> 00:05:53.970
and the Judicial. which administers
justice through the law.

74
00:05:54.410 --> 00:05:56.547
To prevent centralized power.

75
00:05:56.630 --> 00:05:58.887
they also serve to keep an eye
on each other.

76
00:05:58.970 --> 00:06:01.487
LEGISLATION. EXECUTION. ADJUDICATION
Actually. I've asked Regurd. Rogurd.

77
00:06:01.570 --> 00:06:03.147
LEGISLATION. EXECUTION. ADJUDICATION
and Rugurd to each take the lead.

78
00:06:03.230 --> 00:06:04.900
and Rugurd to each take the lead.

79
00:06:05.480 --> 00:06:07.737
Is everyone keeping up so far?

80
00:06:07.820 --> 00:06:08.817
Of course!

81
00:06:08.900 --> 00:06:10.067
Are you?

82
00:06:10.150 --> 00:06:11.280
Sir!

83
00:06:12.530 --> 00:06:14.490
You'll get a make-up class later!

84
00:06:15.120 --> 00:06:16.657
That's exactly what I was hoping for!

85
00:06:16.740 --> 00:06:19.120
I feel like you're
misunderstanding this.

86
00:06:19.740 --> 00:06:23.667
Well. I'm also still studying this
with Rigurd. though.

87
00:06:23.750 --> 00:06:25.297
Oh. speaking of which.

88
00:06:25.380 --> 00:06:26.427
I'm going to set up

89
00:06:26.510 --> 00:06:27.507
PROSECUTOR
a Prosecutor's Office in the executive branch

90
00:06:27.590 --> 00:06:28.537
PROSECUTOR
and a Court in the judicial branch...

91
00:06:28.620 --> 00:06:31.010
COURT
and a Court in the judicial branch...

92
00:06:31.620 --> 00:06:35.847
But it's really tough to choose the right
people to lead these two bodies...

93
00:06:35.930 --> 00:06:37.927
Is there a problem?

94
00:06:38.010 --> 00:06:39.227
Yeah.

95
00:06:39.310 --> 00:06:40.057
It's about...

96
00:06:40.140 --> 00:06:41.807
ATTORNEY GENERAL
the Attorney General. who cracks down on crime.

97
00:06:41.890 --> 00:06:42.557
ATTORNEY GENERAL
and the Chief Justice

98
00:06:42.640 --> 00:06:44.957
CHIEF JUSTICE OF THE SUPREME COURT
of the Supreme Court. who renders judgment.

99
00:06:45.040 --> 00:06:48.067
Those are positions that are
likely to draw resentment.

100
00:06:48.150 --> 00:06:49.667
Monsters. after all.
- You did something bad. so you're guilty.

101
00:06:49.750 --> 00:06:51.987
obey the law of survival of the fittest.
- You did something bad. so you're guilty.

102
00:06:52.070 --> 00:06:52.687
So if we employ
- You know what that means?

103
00:06:52.770 --> 00:06:54.067
a weaker monster to throw the book...
- Go to hell!

104
00:06:54.150 --> 00:06:56.490
Whaaaaat?!

105
00:06:57.740 --> 00:07:02.207
I see. It would be difficult
if they can't protect themselves.

106
00:07:02.290 --> 00:07:05.877
Many races with strong administrative
skills are physically weak.

107
00:07:05.960 --> 00:07:10.750
whereas combat-oriented races
often struggle with administration.

108
00:07:11.420 --> 00:07:12.877
That's right...

109
00:07:12.960 --> 00:07:15.507
What a dilemma.

110
00:07:15.590 --> 00:07:17.007
Yeah...

111
00:07:17.090 --> 00:07:20.290
Speaking of. we are in dire
need of one more person. actually...

112
00:07:20.680 --> 00:07:22.057
Which is...

113
00:07:22.140 --> 00:07:24.897
The military envoy
dispatched to the Council.

114
00:07:24.980 --> 00:07:26.270
The military envoy?

115
00:07:26.750 --> 00:07:30.437
The councilor who will take my place
in coordinating the Western nations.

116
00:07:30.520 --> 00:07:33.190
I wonder who I should send...

117
00:07:35.450 --> 00:07:39.197
Ideally. I'd like a mediator
who's smart. sociable.

118
00:07:39.280 --> 00:07:43.997
has a certain degree of charisma.
and is also capable in combat.

119
00:07:44.080 --> 00:07:47.450
But who here possesses such qualities...

120
00:07:50.490 --> 00:07:51.417
Diablo?

121
00:07:51.500 --> 00:07:52.547
That's true.

122
00:07:52.630 --> 00:07:54.467
He's a good candidate.

123
00:07:54.550 --> 00:07:57.257
Certainly. if that troublemaker
were to step down.

124
00:07:57.340 --> 00:08:00.047
the importance of the First Secretary
would increase.

125
00:08:00.130 --> 00:08:01.977
There couldn't be
a better candidate!

126
00:08:02.060 --> 00:08:04.560
Getting personal. aren't you?

127
00:08:07.800 --> 00:08:09.007
But. man.

128
00:08:09.090 --> 00:08:13.470
He went looking for a subordinate
'cause he hated this kind of work.

129
00:08:27.620 --> 00:08:29.820
Gaia...

130
00:08:39.289 --> 00:08:40.917
Have you been
to the new cafeteria yet?

131
00:08:41.000 --> 00:08:41.966
Yeah. that place's good.

132
00:08:42.049 --> 00:08:45.540
Well. worrying about people
who aren't here is pointless.

133
00:08:46.250 --> 00:08:48.400
This is the perfect time
for an inspection!

134
00:08:49.190 --> 00:08:51.150
W-What on earth?!

135
00:08:53.400 --> 00:08:54.900
What happened. Kurobe?!

136
00:08:55.400 --> 00:08:59.400
Oh. Master Rimuru.
talk about perfect timing!

137
00:09:00.360 --> 00:09:01.327
A sword?

138
00:09:01.410 --> 00:09:04.867
Answer. It has evolved from
the Weapon: Broadsword...

139
00:09:04.950 --> 00:09:07.457
...into the Magic Weapon:
Broadsword.

140
00:09:07.540 --> 00:09:09.080
Magic Weapon?

141
00:09:10.120 --> 00:09:11.580
Wait! Is that...

142
00:09:12.210 --> 00:09:13.917
Yes. it is that!

143
00:09:14.000 --> 00:09:18.300
The sword that you suggested
a while back is finally finished!

144
00:09:19.630 --> 00:09:20.847
It is to your liking. right?

145
00:09:20.930 --> 00:09:25.677
It works by inserting a core
into this hole to grant attributes.

146
00:09:25.760 --> 00:09:28.480
And. there you go.
A magical weapon.

147
00:09:30.150 --> 00:09:32.517
So. these are the cores?

148
00:09:32.600 --> 00:09:33.487
That's right!

149
00:09:33.570 --> 00:09:35.857
The core colors differ
according to their attributes.

150
00:09:35.940 --> 00:09:38.820
I named them Elemental Cores.

151
00:09:39.320 --> 00:09:42.320
and the effects change
based on how you combine them.

152
00:09:43.530 --> 00:09:45.620
So. the explosion just now was...

153
00:09:47.800 --> 00:09:50.860
Well. I'll show you one by one.

154
00:09:51.640 --> 00:09:55.250
Let's start with just one fire core.

155
00:09:56.460 --> 00:09:58.087
Wow!

156
00:09:58.170 --> 00:09:59.830
And that's what you got.

157
00:10:00.360 --> 00:10:01.847
Let's have fire and water.

158
00:10:01.930 --> 00:10:03.970
One core each.

159
00:10:06.850 --> 00:10:08.977
It won't output as much power.

160
00:10:09.060 --> 00:10:10.057
I see.

161
00:10:10.140 --> 00:10:13.140
Now. two fire cores
and one water's.

162
00:10:20.320 --> 00:10:22.737
It will increase the power output tenfold.

163
00:10:22.820 --> 00:10:24.867
That was indubitably
a steam explosion.

164
00:10:24.950 --> 00:10:25.867
Notice.

165
00:10:25.950 --> 00:10:28.617
Depending on which
Elemental Cores are combined.

166
00:10:28.700 --> 00:10:31.667
it is estimated that its power could be
on par with a Legend-grade item.

167
00:10:31.750 --> 00:10:34.460
Really?! That's awesome!

168
00:10:34.850 --> 00:10:37.797
I bet there are other wild
combinations out there. too...

169
00:10:37.880 --> 00:10:39.710
Oh. that's right!

170
00:10:42.560 --> 00:10:45.590
There's also something
I wanted to show you. Kurobe.

171
00:10:48.390 --> 00:10:53.057
Gold?! No. wait.
This glow must be...

172
00:10:53.140 --> 00:10:56.630
It was glowing like this
during the last battle as well.

173
00:10:57.590 --> 00:11:00.527
Answer. It's Divine Steel. Hihi'irokane.

174
00:11:00.610 --> 00:11:01.820
Hihi'irokane?

175
00:11:02.680 --> 00:11:04.617
So it is hihi'irokane!

176
00:11:04.700 --> 00:11:08.977
It's a legendary metal said to possess
eternal and unchanging properties.

177
00:11:09.060 --> 00:11:11.960
Wow. I didn't know that
this was such a big deal.

178
00:11:12.700 --> 00:11:14.997
Would you call this
a Legend-grade item. then?

179
00:11:15.080 --> 00:11:19.290
Master Rimuru.
this one is far beyond that...

180
00:11:19.800 --> 00:11:22.087
Which is the level of a mythical-class.
The God-grade.

181
00:11:22.170 --> 00:11:25.217
This one might as well
reach that level.

182
00:11:25.300 --> 00:11:26.300
Huh?

183
00:11:26.680 --> 00:11:28.050
Are you serious?!

184
00:11:29.190 --> 00:11:30.940
What a piece of good news that was.

185
00:11:31.160 --> 00:11:33.300
Got me pumped up!

186
00:11:34.190 --> 00:11:36.840
The station construction's
also going smoothly there.

187
00:11:38.610 --> 00:11:41.480
So this will be the path
that leads to Eurazania. huh?

188
00:11:43.320 --> 00:11:44.560
All right!

189
00:11:45.070 --> 00:11:47.360
ANIMAL KINGDOM OF EURAZANIA

190
00:11:49.280 --> 00:11:50.497
Wow!

191
00:11:50.580 --> 00:11:53.290
We're already this far along?!

192
00:11:57.070 --> 00:11:58.027
Then. the next is...

193
00:11:58.110 --> 00:11:59.067
Geld!

194
00:11:59.150 --> 00:11:59.950
Hm?

195
00:12:00.740 --> 00:12:02.497
Heya. long time no see!

196
00:12:02.580 --> 00:12:04.330
Greetings. Master Rimuru!

197
00:12:05.000 --> 00:12:06.747
Thank you for visiting us.

198
00:12:06.830 --> 00:12:08.957
Be careful over there!

199
00:12:09.040 --> 00:12:10.080
Yeah!

200
00:12:10.670 --> 00:12:14.257
I can't believe the foundation
work is already done.

201
00:12:14.340 --> 00:12:15.547
Yes.

202
00:12:15.630 --> 00:12:18.167
The majins are giving their all.

203
00:12:18.250 --> 00:12:22.377
And it's all thanks to your words
of encouragement. Master Rimuru.

204
00:12:22.460 --> 00:12:23.517
My words?

205
00:12:23.600 --> 00:12:25.020
Of course!

206
00:12:25.800 --> 00:12:29.437
Actually. not long after
construction began.

207
00:12:29.520 --> 00:12:33.777
many of the majins didn't seem to be
putting their all into their work.

208
00:12:33.860 --> 00:12:35.610
Were they?

209
00:12:36.210 --> 00:12:39.277
That was definitely a real test
for you as a boss...

210
00:12:39.360 --> 00:12:40.737
It was.

211
00:12:40.820 --> 00:12:44.870
So I decided to listen
to their complaints.

212
00:12:45.330 --> 00:12:47.120
By that. do you mean...

213
00:12:48.210 --> 00:12:51.297
Yes. We shared a drink.

214
00:12:51.380 --> 00:12:52.997
Oh. right!

215
00:12:53.080 --> 00:12:55.427
That reminds me.
I did have a drink with you. didn't I?

216
00:12:55.510 --> 00:12:55.927
Yes!

217
00:12:56.010 --> 00:12:58.047
Then. how was it?

218
00:12:58.130 --> 00:13:00.807
I was able to hear
their honest feelings.

219
00:13:00.890 --> 00:13:03.387
Since their time under Clayman's rule.

220
00:13:03.470 --> 00:13:07.167
they fear that they would be purged
once we finished the construction.

221
00:13:07.250 --> 00:13:08.920
I see...

222
00:13:10.060 --> 00:13:13.387
They're just like us Orcs.

223
00:13:13.470 --> 00:13:17.650
That's why I told them my own story.

224
00:13:18.150 --> 00:13:22.077
About the sins we Orcs committed.
the demise of the Orc Lord.

225
00:13:22.160 --> 00:13:27.120
and how you gave us a place
to call home. Master Rimuru.

226
00:13:28.580 --> 00:13:29.950
So that's how it is.

227
00:13:30.910 --> 00:13:32.747
We're progressing ahead of schedule.

228
00:13:32.830 --> 00:13:33.987
Yeah. we can't let those guys.

229
00:13:34.070 --> 00:13:36.247
...from the West District beat us.
- I'm really glad I entrusted you

230
00:13:36.330 --> 00:13:38.997
as the site supervisor. Geld.

231
00:13:39.080 --> 00:13:40.847
Thank you for your trust!

232
00:13:40.930 --> 00:13:44.967
I am the one who is grateful
for the opportunity I was given.

233
00:13:45.050 --> 00:13:46.727
Supervisor!

234
00:13:46.810 --> 00:13:49.267
We're done here. could you
please come and have a look?

235
00:13:49.350 --> 00:13:50.517
Sure!

236
00:13:50.600 --> 00:13:52.197
Go ahead. Geld.

237
00:13:52.280 --> 00:13:53.507
Sir!

238
00:13:53.590 --> 00:13:54.860
Please excuse me.

239
00:13:57.020 --> 00:13:59.920
I think I've done it according
to the instructions. but...

240
00:14:00.020 --> 00:14:02.990
Now then. let's check out the rest.

241
00:14:03.530 --> 00:14:08.707
BOUND FOR THALION

242
00:14:08.790 --> 00:14:12.040
BOUND FOR ENGRASSIA
When people grow. technology advances.

243
00:14:12.690 --> 00:14:14.497
and goods circulate
better among countries.

244
00:14:14.580 --> 00:14:17.040
everyone will live more prosperously.

245
00:14:17.560 --> 00:14:19.327
BOUND FOR DWARGON
I hope the connections

246
00:14:19.410 --> 00:14:20.607
BOUND FOR DWARGON
between countries will deepen.

247
00:14:20.690 --> 00:14:22.940
BOUND FOR DWARGON
with Tempest at the center.

248
00:14:24.050 --> 00:14:26.427
KINGDOM OF FALMENACE

249
00:14:26.510 --> 00:14:30.017
Thank you for your visit.
Your Majesty Rimuru.

250
00:14:30.100 --> 00:14:34.197
I was just inspecting
the progress of the track laying.

251
00:14:34.280 --> 00:14:36.647
and I ended up visiting this site. too.

252
00:14:36.730 --> 00:14:38.440
I see.

253
00:14:38.920 --> 00:14:41.130
How was the situation on site?

254
00:14:41.550 --> 00:14:44.050
Everyone is putting in
their best effort.

255
00:14:44.530 --> 00:14:47.157
I see that you've been
giving it your all. too. Mjurran.

256
00:14:47.240 --> 00:14:50.140
It's only natural when you consider
the national interest.

257
00:14:50.310 --> 00:14:55.420
We'd like to be able to immediately
assist in the unlikely event of famine.

258
00:14:56.830 --> 00:14:58.257
Isn't that impressive?

259
00:14:58.340 --> 00:15:00.757
This totally puts me in a tough spot.

260
00:15:00.840 --> 00:15:04.637
Surely you've been giving your all
in studying to become king as well. no?

261
00:15:04.720 --> 00:15:10.227
Well. the thing is.
I have very strict teachers.

262
00:15:10.310 --> 00:15:13.397
I envy you who can travel
around on your own.

263
00:15:13.480 --> 00:15:20.147
Once Edgar grows up. I'll finally
break free from this stuffy king role.

264
00:15:20.230 --> 00:15:24.157
Your Majesty Youm.
could you please mind your remarks?

265
00:15:24.240 --> 00:15:26.317
Queen Mjur has been
blessed with a child.

266
00:15:26.400 --> 00:15:29.497
It is the norm that the child is the one
who shall succeed to the throne.

267
00:15:29.580 --> 00:15:31.287
Huh? Wait a minute...

268
00:15:31.370 --> 00:15:32.660
A child...

269
00:15:33.500 --> 00:15:34.787
Good heavens. Your Majesty...

270
00:15:34.870 --> 00:15:37.917
Did you not inform the very person
who has done you such a great favor?

271
00:15:38.000 --> 00:15:39.337
I mean...

272
00:15:39.420 --> 00:15:40.750
You get me. right?

273
00:15:41.670 --> 00:15:46.510
It's just. I felt a little embarrassed
to be the one to bear the news...

274
00:15:48.010 --> 00:15:49.427
Good grief...

275
00:15:49.510 --> 00:15:53.430
Congratulations. you both.
I'm truly happy for you.

276
00:15:53.690 --> 00:15:54.807
Thank you.

277
00:15:54.890 --> 00:15:56.440
Thank you very much.

278
00:15:57.380 --> 00:15:59.860
Wait. so Grucius was...

279
00:16:01.230 --> 00:16:05.397
It seems that the news was too much
of a shock for Commander Grucius.

280
00:16:05.480 --> 00:16:07.327
I-I see...

281
00:16:07.410 --> 00:16:09.620
My deepest condolences. Grucius.

282
00:16:11.590 --> 00:16:14.117
Rimuru! Bad news!

283
00:16:14.200 --> 00:16:15.577
Gosh. can't you chill?

284
00:16:15.660 --> 00:16:16.917
Anyway. what's so sudden?

285
00:16:17.000 --> 00:16:19.497
Just hurry back. all right?!

286
00:16:19.580 --> 00:16:21.207
This is of the utmost importance.

287
00:16:21.290 --> 00:16:22.910
Utmost importance. you say?

288
00:16:27.550 --> 00:16:28.890
95TH FLOOR UNDERGROUND - RESEARCH FACILITY
Come on. hurry up!

289
00:16:29.640 --> 00:16:31.967
Geez. you are so slow!

290
00:16:32.050 --> 00:16:33.807
Over here. Rimuru!

291
00:16:33.890 --> 00:16:35.937
Can you both just tell me what it is?

292
00:16:36.020 --> 00:16:37.857
It's a really big deal!

293
00:16:37.940 --> 00:16:39.730
Yeah! Just hurry up
and come here.

294
00:16:40.230 --> 00:16:41.440
Okay. okay.

295
00:16:42.360 --> 00:16:45.910
You both better not have called me
over here for some stupid reasons...

296
00:16:46.860 --> 00:16:48.320
Hey. Veldora!

297
00:16:49.290 --> 00:16:50.320
He's gone?

298
00:16:51.700 --> 00:16:53.700
What are they up to now?

299
00:17:01.820 --> 00:17:02.757
Whoa!

300
00:17:02.840 --> 00:17:04.839
W-What is that?!

301
00:17:19.560 --> 00:17:20.647
Is this what I think it is?

302
00:17:20.730 --> 00:17:22.937
It is what you think this is!

303
00:17:23.020 --> 00:17:25.317
It's finally finished!

304
00:17:25.400 --> 00:17:27.107
This. is the prototype of...

305
00:17:27.190 --> 00:17:29.697
Magitrain No. 0!

306
00:17:29.780 --> 00:17:31.527
No. 0!

307
00:17:31.610 --> 00:17:33.950
Huh? H-How?!

308
00:17:34.660 --> 00:17:37.270
How is it. Rimuru?
You were surprised. right?

309
00:17:42.570 --> 00:17:46.000
How is it moving?!
The power reactor isn't even...

310
00:17:46.310 --> 00:17:47.287
Notice.

311
00:17:47.370 --> 00:17:51.637
The elemental core of the Magitrain
is operating as its power source.

312
00:17:51.720 --> 00:17:53.687
Is it really the elemental core?

313
00:17:53.770 --> 00:17:55.517
I expect no less from you.
Master Rimuru.

314
00:17:55.600 --> 00:17:58.100
You got it figured out. I see.

315
00:17:58.510 --> 00:18:01.897
But how?! It's not something
that can be done so easily...

316
00:18:01.980 --> 00:18:04.857
We thought so too.

317
00:18:04.940 --> 00:18:09.817
Thanks to E.C. my masterpiece.
we've made a breakthrough!

318
00:18:09.900 --> 00:18:13.907
The power core of Lady Ramiris'
Elemental Colossus...

319
00:18:13.990 --> 00:18:18.327
...was based on the same theory
as the elemental core.

320
00:18:18.410 --> 00:18:21.327
I see! Now that you mentioned it...

321
00:18:21.410 --> 00:18:25.837
Guess what happened after we finished
analyzing your Master Core's design?

322
00:18:25.920 --> 00:18:27.967
Before we knew it.

323
00:18:28.050 --> 00:18:31.837
we had finished building a power reactor
that harnesses elemental power...

324
00:18:31.920 --> 00:18:34.927
That is the elemental core.

325
00:18:35.010 --> 00:18:37.510
That's an impressive feat
for such a short time...

326
00:18:39.020 --> 00:18:42.187
I hope you don't forget
my achievements as well.

327
00:18:42.270 --> 00:18:44.437
Pardon me. your achievements?

328
00:18:44.520 --> 00:18:45.777
Yes.

329
00:18:45.860 --> 00:18:49.197
Since this requires immense
firepower for practical use.

330
00:18:49.280 --> 00:18:51.987
we had him summon a salamander.

331
00:18:52.070 --> 00:18:55.910
That means the train couldn't
have operated without me.

332
00:18:58.410 --> 00:19:01.327
So Veldora summoned a salamander...

333
00:19:01.410 --> 00:19:04.087
It wasn't hassle-free. though.

334
00:19:04.170 --> 00:19:08.087
Turns out. summoning a fire spirit
inside the furnace wasn't enough.

335
00:19:08.170 --> 00:19:10.297
We also had to automate
the power control and stuff.

336
00:19:10.380 --> 00:19:12.087
There were so many hurdles. but...

337
00:19:12.170 --> 00:19:15.680
This is a huge victory
for Elemental Engineering!

338
00:19:16.070 --> 00:19:17.660
Power control...?

339
00:19:18.550 --> 00:19:19.680
Ah!

340
00:19:29.440 --> 00:19:30.277
Whoa!

341
00:19:30.360 --> 00:19:32.817
You all even got the pressure
of the boiler stable. too!

342
00:19:32.900 --> 00:19:35.900
Looks like you've got everything
under perfect control!

343
00:19:36.360 --> 00:19:38.787
I feel both happy and sad.

344
00:19:38.870 --> 00:19:42.617
The elemental core I once
wanted to use for the Magisoldiers

345
00:19:42.700 --> 00:19:45.170
has been completed this easily.

346
00:19:45.660 --> 00:19:50.380
But look. it's because of that incident
that we are where we are today.

347
00:19:50.920 --> 00:19:54.770
What we were lacking wasn't theory.

348
00:19:57.300 --> 00:20:00.657
Because of that. I've acquired
the reactor of my dreams.

349
00:20:00.740 --> 00:20:01.810
Hey. now!

350
00:20:02.270 --> 00:20:04.267
Are the deployment tests
moving forward as well?

351
00:20:04.350 --> 00:20:05.347
Yes.

352
00:20:05.430 --> 00:20:08.357
We are working on this together
with the magic researchers.

353
00:20:08.440 --> 00:20:11.737
Leave the environmental testing to us.

354
00:20:11.820 --> 00:20:15.157
This is where our expertise
in Magic Research comes in.

355
00:20:15.240 --> 00:20:17.657
So this is Thalion's Sorcerous Science...

356
00:20:17.740 --> 00:20:20.907
We're done collecting
and analyzing the data. too.

357
00:20:20.990 --> 00:20:22.740
You guys are...

358
00:20:23.290 --> 00:20:25.077
They are the Vampire's Surmounter.

359
00:20:25.160 --> 00:20:29.587
It's great that our Physics Engineering
came in handy!

360
00:20:29.670 --> 00:20:31.337
He's quite a character.

361
00:20:31.420 --> 00:20:37.170
Anyway. thanks to them.
we've finally got the theory sorted out.

362
00:20:37.680 --> 00:20:40.097
Which means. what's left is actually...

363
00:20:40.180 --> 00:20:41.267
Yeah!

364
00:20:41.350 --> 00:20:44.017
We just have to wait until
the rails are finished!

365
00:20:44.100 --> 00:20:46.430
We can do a test run anytime!

366
00:20:48.810 --> 00:20:52.707
The theory is taking shape with
all kinds of environments simulated

367
00:20:52.790 --> 00:20:54.710
and with the data analyzed.

368
00:20:55.230 --> 00:20:58.527
If even one piece is missing.
we wouldn't have made it this far...

369
00:20:58.610 --> 00:21:01.690
This is the pinnacle of our
technological expertise!

370
00:21:02.620 --> 00:21:04.290
And... go!

371
00:21:06.790 --> 00:21:07.910
Whoa!

372
00:21:09.170 --> 00:21:11.587
By the way. Master...

373
00:21:11.670 --> 00:21:15.127
Now that the prototype's done.
it is worth celebrating.

374
00:21:15.210 --> 00:21:16.627
How should I say it...

375
00:21:16.710 --> 00:21:20.970
I wish we could throw a party for this.

376
00:21:22.850 --> 00:21:24.767
You can bet I'd say a loud yes!

377
00:21:24.850 --> 00:21:27.790
Let's throw a big one today!

378
00:21:29.680 --> 00:21:34.860
♪ Things like peace of mind and joy ♪

379
00:21:35.300 --> 00:21:40.777
♪ I was enveloped in such emotions ♪

380
00:21:40.860 --> 00:21:46.287
♪ We can talk later ♪

381
00:21:46.370 --> 00:21:50.877
♪ After the wind has died down a bit ♪

382
00:21:50.960 --> 00:21:57.337
♪ Days gone by. leaving
the trails they wove ♪

383
00:21:57.420 --> 00:22:02.637
♪ Tomorrow will surely be irreplaceable ♪

384
00:22:02.720 --> 00:22:08.637
♪ Where have the greedy
clouds drifted off to? ♪

385
00:22:08.720 --> 00:22:13.817
♪ If no one can tell. then ♪

386
00:22:13.900 --> 00:22:19.277
♪ Walk on your way ♪

387
00:22:19.360 --> 00:22:24.987
♪ Embrace this very moment ♪

388
00:22:25.070 --> 00:22:30.327
♪ One step ahead of your future ♪

389
00:22:30.410 --> 00:22:36.380
♪ Continuing this story ♪

390
00:22:39.210 --> 00:22:42.387
She is hatching. She is hatching!

391
00:22:42.470 --> 00:22:43.507
Milim?!

392
00:22:43.590 --> 00:22:45.767
Rimuru. we have an emergency!

393
00:22:45.850 --> 00:22:47.810
She is hatching soon!

394
00:22:48.430 --> 00:22:50.637
W-What should I do?!

395
00:22:50.720 --> 00:22:52.557
C-Calm down. Milim!

396
00:22:52.640 --> 00:22:55.230
Oh my!
I'll bring some clothes!

397
00:22:57.130 --> 00:23:00.837
♪ I'll believe in you ♪

398
00:23:00.920 --> 00:23:03.727
♪ Repeating the next step ♪

399
00:23:03.810 --> 00:23:10.207
♪ I want to layer the sky
etched in my memory ♪

400
00:23:10.290 --> 00:23:16.520
♪ Let's go together ♪

401
00:23:18.190 --> 00:23:23.570
♪ Walk on your way ♪

402
00:23:24.510 --> 00:23:25.630
Gaia...

403
00:23:29.180 --> 00:23:34.370
♪ One step ahead of your future ♪

404
00:23:35.270 --> 00:23:37.850
There are many challenges
we need to overcome.

405
00:23:38.270 --> 00:23:39.670
But even so...

406
00:23:41.320 --> 00:23:46.370
Everyone. meet my friend. Gaia!

407
00:23:50.350 --> 00:23:52.457
Welcome to Tempest!

408
00:23:52.540 --> 00:23:54.390
We're happy to have you here!

409
00:24:02.550 --> 00:24:05.927
THAT TIME I GOT REINCARNATED
AS A SLIME SEASON 4

410
00:24:06.010 --> 00:24:09.410
Next time: New Friends.

